-- Hooters Food Chain Plans Russian Franchise, Kommersant Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-03-06T04:59:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/hooters-food-chain-plans-russian-franchise-kommersant-says.html
Hooters of America Inc., the
restaurant chain best known for its tank top-clad waitresses,
plans to expand into  Russia ,  Kommersant  reported, citing
unidentified people familiar with the matter.  The company is seeking a local partner and has approached
Anton Viner, the step-son of billionaire Alisher Usmanov who
owns Uzbek restaurants in Moscow and other Russian cities, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  